      "writtenOn": "2017-04-03T15:55:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "pid_t isn’t generically correct here, and won’t really work at all for macOS.\n\nWould a ProcessSnapshot be enough? That’d be a nice generic interface, and I think would at least force downstream code into the right mindset to evolve this further. If it’s not enough, then I’d like to at least provide it in addition to the HANDLE, and perhaps just “hide” the HANDLE in ProcessSnapshotWin by exposing a GetProcessHandle() getter over there so that you can reinterpret_cast the ProcessSnapshot* you get to ProcessSnapshotWin*.",
      "revId": "1b1168a03c72546d77c37b28a5e28d002047eda1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
